First, create a repo in git
Name it something like:
jenkins-maven-demo

(STRUCTURE:
  jenkins-maven-demo/
 ├── Jenkinsfile
 ├── pom.xml
 └── src
     └── main
         └── java
             └── App.java
)

File 1: Jenkinsfile
pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {
        stage('Clone Repository') {
            steps {
                git 'https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/jenkins-maven-demo'
            }
        }

        stage('Build with Maven') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean install'
            }
        }

        stage('Run') {
            steps {
                sh 'echo "Build completed successfully!"'
            }
        }
    }
}

File 2: pom.xml
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>demo</groupId>
    <artifactId>jenkins-maven-demo</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.8.1</version>
                <configuration>
                    <source>8</source>
                    <target>8</target>
                </configuration>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>

</project>

File 3: Java Code
Go to:
src/main/java/
Create a file named App.java
public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello from Jenkins + Maven!");
    }
}


STEP 4 — Jenkins Setup (finally)
Open Jenkins
Click New Item
Enter a name: Maven-Pipeline-Demo
Choose Pipeline
Scroll to Pipeline section
Choose: Pipeline script from SCM
Select Git
Paste your repo URL
Save
Click Build Now


